# Figma to Next.js Conversion Rules

## Rule 1: Never Use Hardcoded Figma Values in Styles

```typescript
// ‚ùå WRONG ‚Äì Direct Figma values
const Box = styled.div`
  color: #3b82f6;
  font-size: 24px;
  padding: 32px;
  border-radius: 8px;
`;

// ‚úÖ CORRECT ‚Äì Design system (COLORS, TYPOGRAPHY, SPACING)
const Box = styled.div`
  color: ${COLORS.PRIMARY};
  ${TYPOGRAPHY.HEADING_H2_BOLD};
  padding: ${SPACING.LG};
  border-radius: ${SPACING.XS};
`;
```

## Rule 2: Figma Frames ‚Üí React/HTML Components

- **Figma Frame** = `<div>`/`<section>` container or a layout component.
- **Figma Component** = Reusable component (e.g. `ProductCard`, `PrimaryButton`).
- **Figma Auto Layout** = CSS flexbox/grid: `display: flex`, `flex-direction`, `align-items`, `justify-content`, `gap`.

## Rule 3: Figma Auto-Layout ‚Üí CSS

- Vertical stack ‚Üí `display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: ...`.
- Horizontal stack ‚Üí `display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: ...`.
- Center align ‚Üí `align-items: center; justify-content: center;`.
- Grid layouts ‚Üí `display: grid; grid-template-columns: ...; gap: ...`.

## Rule 4: Figma Effects ‚Üí CSS

- **Shadow:** `box-shadow: x y blur spread color;` (map color to COLORS token).
- **Opacity:** `opacity`.
- **Blur:** `backdrop-filter: blur(...)` or `filter: blur(...)`.
- **Corner radius:** `border-radius` (prefer spacing/radius tokens).

## Rule 5: Figma Text Styles ‚Üí TYPOGRAPHY (including fontWeight)

Map Figma text styles to project TYPOGRAPHY tokens (e.g. `TYPOGRAPHY.TEXT_PARAGRAPH_14`, `TYPOGRAPHY.HEADING_H1_BOLD`). **Always include fontWeight:** map Figma weight (100‚Äì900) to the correct token (e.g. 400 ‚Üí Regular, 500 ‚Üí Medium, 700 ‚Üí Bold). Do not hardcode font-family/font-size/line-height when a token exists; do not omit font-weight for text.

## Rule 6: Figma Colors ‚Üí COLORS

Map every color to a `COLORS` token (e.g. `COLORS.BACKGROUND_WHITE`, `COLORS.TEXT_PRIMARY`). No raw hex in styles except via the COLORS object.

## Rule 7: Assets

- **SVG icons / vectors** ‚Üí export as React components in `src/assets/icons` (single `Icons` object) or as `.svg` imported with SVGR. No raw inline SVG duplicated across files.
- **Raster images (png/jpg/webp)** ‚Üí place in `public/images/` and render via `next/image` (with `width`/`height` or `fill` + `sizes`). Prefer WebP/optimized formats.

## Rule 8: Error Handling

Use optional chaining: `obj?.value` when accessing nested or optional data (per project rule).

## Responsive (Next.js / Web)

- Use relative units (`rem`, `%`, `clamp()`), CSS media queries, and fluid layouts (flex/grid) for responsiveness across breakpoints.
- Define breakpoints in the theme; reuse them in styled-components media queries.
- Ensure interactive targets are comfortably tappable/clickable (‚âà 44px) and have visible focus states.

## Server vs Client

- Static, presentational sections ‚Üí Server Components.
- Anything with state, handlers, styled-components, or browser APIs ‚Üí Client Component (`'use client'`).

## Validation Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded hex in styles (use COLORS).
- [ ] Typography from TYPOGRAPHY where available; **fontWeight set for every text style** (e.g. 400, 500, 700) per Figma/spec.
- [ ] Layout uses flexbox/grid mapped from Auto Layout.
- [ ] box-shadow / border-radius from tokens where applicable.
- [ ] SVGs as components in `@/assets/icons`; raster images in `public/` via `next/image`.
- [ ] Optional chaining for safe access where appropriate.
- [ ] Correct Server/Client component boundary.
